NewsText.SourceString:
Minor fixes and tweaks:

-XP given per kill is increased by 10%

-Z given at ending screen is increased by 10%

-Base  Earned per wave is increased by 15% from 500 to 575.

-Collision box for pickups (weapons, Zed-Cola, objective pickups etc.) is enlarged by 25% to make it easier to pick it up from the ground.

-Lennart's and The Dude's health is also shown at the left side of the screen, at the objective border.

-Fixed a bug where Zedfoxx (The speaker host) didn't speak after a Map restart/Map switch.

Fixes and features added for 0.42:

-Steam Avatars is now showing correctly in the lobby.

-The Internmission(pause) between waves is now skippable. Everyone in the same game needs to accept the skip by pressing F1.

-Stcky Grenades now sticks onto Zeds correctly.

-Doctor's starting secondary weapon is now Doctor's Arc Rifle instead of Dewolt Syringe pistol.
 
-Doctor's Arc Rifle now have unlimited ammo.

-Torpedo's starting primary weapon, LVL 1 Tri Barrel Bloodshed Gun have been slightly buffed.

-There is a new window at the ending screen showing which team member made the best score, most kills, most headshots etc.

-The Invite code in the lobby is blurred out at default. The blur disappears when hovering over it.
 
-The Chain saw's damage have been slightly increased.

-Your score could sometimes be higher than it should based on your kills and chain multiplier. It was a tiny math fail that is now fixed.

-Sometimes you couldn't pickup/buy ammunition. The Ammo system have seen an overhaul and is now more streamlined and flexible. 

-Z given at ending screen is increased by 20%

Small adjustments and QoL for 0.50:

-Each Chainkill yields x1,05 on the multiplier instead of 1,0. Headsots still yields x2.

-The Detonator's (Small exploding robot's) head stops blinking if it dies without exploding.

-1 New daily and 1 new Seasonal Objective added.

-Amount of blood spurting from the Zeds are increased by 25%.

-A text will pop up when trying to place a Traps n' goodie, telling if it's possible to place it on the ground or not.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.51.

Fixes:
-The Scoreboard window (Tab) could get stuck if you opened Steam overlay at the same time. This is now fixed.

-Fixed an issue where Shooting Zeds very close to you could be problematic, since the bullets comes from the weapons muzzle and not your body you couldn't hit them if very close. This is fixed and works much better now.

-Fixed an issue where you couldn't reload a weapon that you bought from P.U.G.S. It works correctly now.


Changes:
-The Zeds running speed have been reduced by 40% in Scrub difficulty. Playing in Scrub difficulty should be more of a learning experience and to get a feeling of the game, making the player prepared to succeed in higher difficulties.

-Zed Spawn rate have been changed slightly in SOLO mode. 1,4 seconds between each spawn instead of 1,1.

-Hip-fire weapon spread penalty have been reduced by 50%. Making it easier to hit targets even without aiming (Right mouse button).

-Superb Needle Gun's (Doctor's staring primary weapon) projectile's velocity have been increased by 30% and bullet drop have been decreased by 50%. The damage per Syringe have also been increased across all 5 Weapon levels.

-Amount of Zeds needed to be shredded, pressed, lured down the blender etc. have been slightly reduced when there are more than 2 people in the server. 

Added:
- Do you want to play as the wholesome General Manta? Go try to collect him in the Planetarium!
- A Text that pops up when in Ragdoll mode, telling you which button to get out of Ragdoll again.

Tip of the day: You can punch Zeds away by using keyboard button C.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.52.

Fixes:
-Fixed a bug where dropping a weapon on the ground with zero ammo in the magazine and then picking it up again, the weapon had a full magazine.

-Fixed the shower not cleaning off the blood everytime.

-Fixed Zeds getting stuck on certain spots in the Planetarium.

-Fixed the Steam achievement Slice'n'Dice. It is now showing the progress correctly.

-Fixed the Steam achievement Balboa_2.0. It is now working as intended.

Changes:
-Prestige-ing a class not only requires you to be LVL 20, it will also cost you +100Z per Prestige LVL. So LVL 1 is 100Z, LVL 2 is 200Z etc. With a max-price of 1000Z
-Zed drops (Zed-Cola, Piggybank, Ammo box) now have a 3% drop chance instead of 2%. Final wave/Boss wave increases drop chance to 8%.

-Superb Needle Gun's (Doctor's staring primary weapon) and the Dewolt Syringe pistol are now Hitscan weapons instead of shooting projectiles with bullet drop.  

-The Doctor starts with a full pack of Zed-Cola.

-Lowered Max-Ammo for Nuker Primary weapons from 70 to 58, while increasing the ammo price by 8%.

-Changed earned XP for the Class daily challenges from 1000 XP to 4000 XP.

-Lowered the Zeds runspeed in Normal and Hardcore difficulty by 10%, leaving Kamikaze as it is.

-Zed spawn rate is 1.4 seconds per Zed in Solo mode, except for Hardcore or Kamikaze, where it is 1.1 seconds instead.

-The length of the metal bar is shortened.

Added:
-Prestige-ing also gives the selected class +1% for all Level bonus stats and 15% bonus XP per Prestige level.

-Added Sticky Grenades to Doctor's loadout.

-Punch Lennart or The Dude(Escort Objectives) and It'll boost their speed by 100% for 5 seconds. They even have voicelines!

-A little text Showing Difficulty in scoreboard (TAB).

-Difficulty XP multiplier. You now earn more XP per Zed kill in higher difficluties.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.521.

Fixes:
-Fixed the FPS getting worse over time.

Changes:
-Lowered Superb Needle Gun's damage across all levels by 35%.

-Increased the range of the Hefty Sweety Revolver by 25%.

-Lowered Max-Ammo for the Sniper from 130 to 50, while increasing the ammo price by 200%.

Added:
-There is now a Wave multiplier, increasing Zed's damage and health by 1% for each wave.

-There is now a Zed health difficulty multiplier, increasing the Zeds health by 0%/7,5%/12,5%/20% from Scrub/Normal/Hardcore/Kamikaze difficulty.

-There is a blue outline on the last 3 Zeds on the map, making it possible to spot the Zeds through walls.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.522.

Fixes:
-Fixed an ammo bug that happened occasionally, making it impossible to stack up more ammo.

-If you switched inventory extremely quickly you could have 2 items in the hand. Fixed

-Added a few collision boxes at places players aren't supposed to be at.

-Fixed Hitboxes for the melee weapons. There could be some problems to hit if standing too close to the Zed.

Changes:

Changed the A.I a little bit, they now jump down ledges and other floors instead of just finding the path to you on the ground. You will notice it most at Maps with height differences, such as Blackcube Lair or the Planetarium.

-Increased Tri Barrel Bloodshed Gun's and the Double barrel Shotgun's damage For LVL 1.

-Increased Superb Needle Gun's damage across all levels just a tad bit since last update. Seems to be well balanced now.

-Decreased Dewolt Syringe pistol's damage by like, alot. Did way too much damage before.

-Increased Max-Ammo for the Sniper from 50 to 80.

Added:

-New Steam Achievement, I'm on top of the Alien! Stand on top of the Statue in the Planetarium for 5 seconds.

-New Steam Achievement, The Zed King! Score a total of 1,000,000.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.53.

Fixes:

- Fixed the Mouse sensitivity slider in Settings > controls. It is now working as intended. Default sensitivity is also decreased about 40%.

- Fixed several collisions on meshes and added collisions at places players aren't supposed to be at.

- Fixed both Zedfoxx's doors flickering when opened.

- Fixed a bug that made you have more ammunition than allowed when using a specific perk, which also made it possible to sell ammunition at P.U.G.S and exceed max-cap .

- Fixed an issue when in Customization menu you could be at the Secondary weapon tab first, and when jumping to another class and back it shows Primary weapons but secondary button is still selected.

- Rocket shots from Zeds went above your head if standing fairly close. Fixed

- Fixed a bug where sometimes the clients didn't receive damage from Zeds.

- Fixed a bug where sometimes the clients didn't see flying rockets from shooting Zeds. 


Changes:

- Changed Bonebreaker's Health from 200 to 150 and Armor from 150 to 110.

- Trax 5 Grenade Pistol's explosive radius have been reduced from 325cm to 250cm

- Hefty Sweety Revolver's recoil have been reduced by 30% across all weapon-levels.

- Reduced recoil on all different Shotguns and different pistols.

- Lowered Max-Ammo for Nuker Primary weapons from 58 to 42, while increasing the ammo price by 30%.

- All classes now start with the weapons current Max ammo-cap.

- The perk that increased Max starting Ammo for selected classes now increases Max carrying ammo too. So you can buy/pickup and carry more ammunition with that perk selected.

- Everybody that hits and kills the same Zed receives the same score and XP. Earlier only the one that got the killing blow recieved full score and XP.

- Optimized Blood spurts from Zeds. Much more performant now.

- Instead of being unequipped when you have used all your grenades or health packs, you now swap to the next item in Inventory instead.

- Increased Pistol ammo price at P.U.G.S by 50%.

- If a Zed drop occur, there is 60% chance to be an Ammo box, 20% to be a Piggy Bank and 20% to be a Zed-Cola.



Added:

- The weapon upgrade system have been redesigned, you have to use the weapon and get kills with it to be able to upgrade it. You still have to pay for the upgrades but you can't do it until you have enough kills with the gun. You can Prestige it when Max-level (5) to get a small reward.

- Added a Player kick list in the Pause menu for the Host.

- There is now a voting option to "pause" a multiplayer game (F2). If everyone is ready again, press the usual F1 to continue the Zed Mayhem!

- Specified Zed spawning in Endless Horde mode. For each new wave starting from wave 3, there is 18% chance for a specified Zed spawn, meaning only 1 type of Zed will spawn in that particular wave. Currently there are 3 types of Zeds that may spawn: The Creeper, the Fleshman or the Fat chef.

- 8 Fully fleshed out Perks for the Bonebreaker class!

- A new Zed enemy: the Robotic Granada X2000. Shoots sticky grenades at the players. 75 Base Health. Low spawnrate.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.531.

Fixes:

- Fixed Weapon Prestige Level text showing the wrong level.

- Doctor's Arc Rifle can now level up as the other weapons. Instead of weapon kills, this weapon needs Healing points to level up, which you get by healing your teammates. Healing other players now also rewards XP.

- Server Browser properties in the Main menu (Mapname, difficulty, wave amount etc.) is now updating correctly as the host changes these properties from the lobby.

Changes:

- Reworked and made the chat window much more intuitive.

- Lots of optimizations done for both GPU and CPU. About 5-15% higher framerate (depending on hardware), and hosting a multiplayer game is now less performance intense.

- Lowered Max-Ammo for Nuker Primary weapons from 42 to 36.

- You can no longer sprint when having the DIY Zero-G Gun equipped in your hands.

- The Wave multiplier now increases Zed's damage and health by 2% each wave instead of 1%.

- Increased the Robotic Granada X2000's base health to 125 (75 before).

Added:

- New unlockable character! Can be bought with the new currency you get if prestige:ing a weapon.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.532.

Fixes:

- Fixed a bug when crouching against a wall/corner and then uncrouching, you would still be in crouching state.

- Fixed an exploit where you could switch class at P.U.G.S, sell all the gear, switch again and again etc. to cheat your way to max -cap. You are now only allowed to do one class-switch per internmission.

- Fixed a bug where the purchase confirmation overlay(when buying a character, upgrading weapon, switching class at P-U.G.S etc.) would remain visible if the game started or P.U.G.S closes.

- Disabled SteamVR application popping up when starting the game.

- Fixed LVL 4's Explosive CatBoomer max-ammo being super low.

- A few other tweaks and fixes here and there.

Changes:

- All the weapons are now also upgradable through P.U.G.S, so you no longer need to end the game to upgrade/prestige your weapons.

- Max Zed-cap is lowered from 469 to 420 when playing 4 people at the hardest difficulty, Kamikaze. 

- Doctor's Arc Rifle now yields score to the player when using it. Getting score=  to use at P.U.G.S.

- Nerfed ALL weapons in Nuker's loadout. 

- The camera shake from explosions now change its magnitude depending on the explosive radius. So a smaller explosion = less camera shake.

- Now both Weapon Spread and Weapon Recoil is reduced by 50% when aiming(RMB).

- Further optimizations, improving framerates when there are a lot of stuff happening on the screen at the same time.

Added:

- Explosive Radius text for weapons with explosives in the Customization menu.

- New Steam Achievement: Camera Hater NR.1. Shoot and destroy 500 cameras.

- New Daily Challenge: what's up with the cameras? Shoot down 40 cameras. Rewards you with 12 .

- Shooting down a camera now yields 200 Score. And they respawn after 80 seconds.


Tip of the day: If you kill more Zeds, you'll have Phil Swift in no time!

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.533.

Fixes:

- Fixed the Cameras placed on the maps not rotating correctly after they have been destroyed and respawned.

- Fixed the Traps n' goodies not being placed correctly on the ground but you lost it from inventory when trying to place it. Only happened very occasionally but could happen.

- Fixed the chat window not following the wrapped text correctly, so you could miss out on messages.

- You can no longer Make a Emote or Revive a playing while mid-air. You have to stand on the ground.

- Sometimes when jumping with nuker the bullet explodes right after shooting. Fixed

- Fixed a problem where ESC didn't work in P.U.G.S until clicking anywhere on the screen with the mouse. It now works correctly.

- Fixed the Character sinking into the ground when switching class many times in the lobby/customization menu.

- Sometimes (extremely rare), Zeds could spawn even though the wave was finished. Fixed.

- Sometimes the Server Password window could get stuck on the screen. It should be good now.

- Fixed the "PUGS DISCOUNT COUPON" perk to work for everything at P.U.G.S.

- A lot of other small tweaks and fixes.

Changes:

- Boss health multiplier has been changed. The boss will have a health-increase (apart from difficulty multiplier) of 1.75x from 1 to 2 players, 2.125x with 3 players and 2.5x with 4 players. This is a significant nerf since it was at 3.5x with 4 players before. 

- Removed the No-sprint restriction for the Xtreme 101 MiniGun and DIY Zero-G Gun. It is now possible to sprint with them again.

- All pickups, pushing buttons, opening P.U.G.S etc. are now instant. So instead of holding a button for 0,3 sec, you will now instantly interact with items. the exception is when placing an Objective item to its correct place or when reviving a teammate, that still has the timer.

- Changing class at P.U.G.S now cost 1000.

- Reduced the time required to use a Large Med Kit from 5.0 seconds to 3.5 seconds.

- Cameras placed on the maps now only has 1 HP, meaning you will shoot it down with one bullet.

- You can now only Rocket jump with you own rockets/grenades. You can no longer shoot a teammate away and annoying them to death.

- Camera-shake from explosives have been reduced.

- You now get the Golden nuggets (Yellow ) from Prestige:ing your class aswell.  

- The Commando's perk "Hospital Fraud" have been nerfed from increasing max health by 50% to 33% instead.

- The Doctor's perk "First Aid Kit" have been nerfed from 4 from 4 to 2 Large Med Kits.

- The Bonebreaker's perk "Lots of Melee Swings! have been buffed, from healing 1 health point per Zed kill to 4 health points per Zed kill.

Added:

- Discord Rich Presence. Your Zedfest game progress is now shown on Discord. 

- Added a skull as a Prestige-icon.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.54.

Fixes:

- Fixed the Zeds sliding on the ground when attacking a player, they now move their legs at the same time correctly.

- Fixed some issues that could happen between Sprinting and aiming-mode. You could get stuck in aim-walk mode even when holding down the sprint button. The controls feels much smoother and better now.

- Fixed the blur not covering the Invite code 100% in the Lobby.

- Health Dispenser continues to heal a Player even though they have full health. Fixed.

- Fixed a bug that made the wrong Traps n' goodie be placed on the ground if placed too quickly after selecting that slot.

- Sometimes you could get multiple P.U.G.S windows stacked on top of each other. Fixed.

- Added a few collision boxes at places players aren't supposed to be at.


Changes:

- Max characters in the Password or Servername box are now 19 instead of infinite.

- Changed the Class Prestige-reward numbers a little bit. The rewards only increases until Prestige level 10, and Max Class Prestige level is 10.

- Increased the price for every character in the Customization menu.

- Selling items at P.U.G.S now returns 1/3 of a new item instead of 1/2

- Changing class at P.U.G.S now cost 2100.

- Lowered Amount of Zeds to kill each wave by 15% in Hardcore and Kamikaze difficulty.

- New Shootng sound for the M13A7 Dipshit Gun.


Added:

- New Mechanics for the Bosses, making them more interesting and enjoyable to fight against.

- Improved Spawn System. The Zeds no longer spawn near/on the player as could happen before. They now spawn at least 15 meters away from you.

- Level Bonus stats are now fully functional. Health/Armor/Runspeed and Ammo Bonus now increases per increased class level, and when Prestige:ing the class.

- Added a Class-icon to the Scoreboard (TAB). So you can see which class everybody is playing.

- New and Freshly added Daily challenges. 

- A boss is spawned every 6 waves in Endless mode.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.541.

Fixes:

- Fixed a Health bar rounding error. If your health was 0.4, the health bar would show it as 0 as it rounds to the nearest whole number. This is fixed now.

- Ammo boxes and the Ammo generator now show if your weapon already has full ammo. And it switches weapon name text correctly when switching weapon while looking at the ammo box/generator.

- Fixed an issue where some text got stuck on the screen when playing against Glitchface.

- Grenades at P.U.G.S don't show as full even though they're 4/4. This is fixed.

Changes:

- Disabled weapon spread for every weapon except Shotguns which need it when shooting several pellets in one shot and the Minigun. This in return yields a more accurate and precise aim. Recoil persists and gets lower for each Weapon upgrade.

- Clicking on the equipped weapon/inventory item (left side in the lobby) now takes you directly to that particular category in the customization menu.

- Emotes can now be stopped by using WASD.

- The Damage from using the Melee button while using a weapon (Keyboard button C) is greatly reduced to a more reasonable value.

Added:

- Added a max 1000 FPS option in video settings. Before the max FPS could only be 144 FPS.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.542.

Fixes:

- Fixed a bug regarding the Invincible Power-up. There was a possibility to get stuck in invincibility mode. And another one where you didn't receive your Level bonus health when returning to normal. 

- Fixed a bug regarding the Speed Power-up. 

- You could damage MR.Android during his second starting phase using explosives even though you are not supposed to be able to. Fixed. 

- Holstering the weapon and spamming the shoot button at the same time would make the weapon fire automatically from your back. This is now fixed.

- Fixed a bug during Boss wave in Endless mode where too many Zeds is on the Map at the same time.

- Removed an exploit where you could drop all your gear on the ground, change class and sell the new gear that came with that class. You will now keep your current inventory when switching class.

- Traps n' goodies can now be dropped on the ground from your inventory correctly.

- Fixed an issue when spamming the Purchase button at the Ammo/First aid vending machine and not receiving the loot, but still losing the money.

- Fixed a few collisions for some meshes that Zeds could get stuck on.

Changes:

- Lowered the droprate for Power-ups from 1% to 0,5%

- The Healing Grenade have seen an increase in healing from 4 HP/s to 6HP/s. Totaling 60 hp over 10 sec.

- The Player camera have been slightly more centered instead of being way to the right of the player. Making for a more immersive and enjoyable gameplay

- Along with a more centered camera, the character holding the weapons have moved slightly to the right to line up better from the camera to the crosshair. Looks and feels much better now.

- Decreased the cost to switch class at P.U.G.S from 2100 to 1000.

Fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.6

Fixes:

- Fixed a few collisions for some meshes that Players and Zeds could get stuck on.

- Fixed an issue where the weapon would not shoot directly after reloading when still holding the shoot button.

- Fixed an issue where you could place a Traps n' goodie on top of yourself.

Changes:

- Changed and refined several animations, for example normal jogging, pistol running, sword running and freshly added Med kit/Zed cola animations.

- Slightly improved performance on the Planetarium.


Added:

- New playable Map, the Aquaworld! Step inside the largest Aquarium in Zedfest Universe! Take a look at the beautiful fish, or try out one of the wonderful water slides!

- (WIP) Player Sliding! Your character will slide on the ground and puff away everything in its path. Hold Sprint (Left shift) and press keyboard button C to activate the Sliding. Jumping will interrupt the sliding. Pressing C without sprinting activates the regular melee-bash.

- Cheat Code to change to First person Mode! The code is: enterfp. Bear in mind, this is not an official mode and animations etc. are not made for first person mode, this is just for a little bit of fun!

- Swimming! The Aquarium offers a nice and warm pool! Jump in and go for a swim!

- You can now invite your Steam friends directly into your lobby by right clicking their name in the Friend list and selecting Invite to Game.

Hello fellow Zed hunters! Here comes a bunch of stuff,fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.61.

Fixes:

- Fixed an issue where you could shoot a bullet 2 times within split seconds from each other when holding the Shoot button, reloading and still holding the button.

- Fixed an annoying issue when holding the sprint button, quickly pressing the Aim button and shooting the weapon while releasing Aim, you would sprint and shoot at the same time. This is now fixed.

- Added Several collision boxes on placed players aren't supposed to be at, especially in the Aquapark and Cyber Alert!.

- Fixed an issue where you didn't respawn IF falling through the floor in the map Cyber Alert!. 

- Fixed an issue when switching from sniper rifle (while holding RMB) to secondary or any other weapon, the Sniper HUD was still visible.

- Fixed an issue where the Scoreboard (TAB) could get stuck on the screen.

- Fixed an issue where the Bio Chainsaw would continue to run while sprinting.

- If unlucky, You could get stuck inside a Objective mesh (Shredding machine etc.) if it spawned at the same spot you were standing. The player will now be teleported to Player spawn if this happens.

- Fixed a bug regarding the Invincible Power-up and the Speed Power-up. 

- If you pressed "Start Game" and quickly pressed "Change Map" You would get stuck, unable to click anything in the UI. This is now fixed.

- Fixed a bug where the drop chance for Supply drops (Ammo, health and Piggybanks) didn't increase from 3% to 8% during Boss wave in Endless mode.

- Fixed a bug where you could continue to shoot while stunned.

- Fixed a bug regarding showing wrong Total ammo for a weapon.

Changes:

- You can no longer damage the Boss when it spawns or during the cinematic. Only when the cinematic ends.

- Blood stains now get removed when jumping in the pool at Aquaworld!

- Gordon the Chef's (the Fat Zed) Health have been increased by 66%.

- Creeper's chance to stun a player have been increased from 8% per hit to 20%, making them a more prioritized target.

- Changing class at P.U.G.S now cost 700 instead of 1000

- Poison Grenade's Damage is reduced from 10 Damage per second to 5 Damage per second.

- The Suicide option in the Pause Menu now have confirm window to avoid accidental suicide. 

- Commando's and Torpedo's Health Regeneration Perk now yields 2 health points per second instead of 1.

- M24/7 Eco Gun's Recoil have been reduced and Precision increased across all weapon levels. 

- Swedish Hell Bomber's reload time have been reduced across all weapon levels.

- The Ammo Generator's Despawn time is now 10 minutes instead of 6.

Added:

- New Siren Head (Zed enemy) mechanic: When Siren Head's alarm ends and the Zed explodes (10 second fuse time), all nearby Zeds will enter Enrage mode, increasing their Health/Damage by 35%, and Speed by 50%. 

- Bullet Penetration! Hefty Sweety Revolver and all Shotgun/Sniper weapons now have bullet penetration. Up to two targets can be killed with one bullet, the second target receives 60% of the weapon's base damage.

- Removing and replacing several placeholder images with new images for the weapons.

- Showers in the map Aquaworld!

- New Zed Enemy! The Acid Puke Master!! A fairly slow Zed with an Extremely high damage output and Healthpool. He's getting lighter for every puke he does, making him faster each time. Immune to explosives. Pro tip: Aim for the Gas tank sitting at his back (1/15th of Zed HP).

- Player Sliding Speed boost and Parkour Roll! You will now receive a small speed boost when entering Sliding mode, and pressing the Jump button while Sliding will make the player Roll on the ground.

- New weapon! Harry's Auto Popper: Fast shooting Fully automatic Sniper with low Recoil that deals decent amount of Damage. Medium Scope.

- New weapon! Vortex Blaster x2000: Shoots insanely compressed air together with a little bit of Uranium, dealing huge amounts of Damage around its destination. USE WITH CAUTION!

- 4 new Steam Achievements!

- A couple of new Daily challenges!

Coming in the next update:

- Bugfixes

- A new boss

- A new map

-Upgradable melee-weapons

- Fast Refill-option at P.U.G.S

- And more!

Hey there! Just some small changes and fixes of a few things in Zedfest. Version 0.611.

Fixes:

- Fixed an issue where The Acid Puke Master's Gas tank didn't get removed correctly.

- Fixed an issue where the lobby screen could be stuck and placed on top of the ending screen if joining late.

Changes:

- Lowered the Sliding cooldown, so it is possible to Slide almost immediately again.

- Lowered the price for the Vortex Blaster x2000 at P.U.G.S.

- The Vortex Blaster x2000 now only damages Zeds in range and when not obstructed by an obstacle, making it a little bit less Overpowered but still a very viable option.

Hey all! Just some small changes and fixes of a few things in Zedfest. Version 0.612.

Fixes:

- Fixed an issue where the Zeds skin would change upon death, meaning it was not the same color as when the Zed were alive.

- Fixed an issue with the Parkour Roll Daily Challenge.

- Fixed a game-crash whenS scrolling through your inventory when only having a Zed-Cola, Large Med kit or a Traps n' goodie in inventory.

- Fixed an issue where the Crosshair didn't reappear after Sliding/Rolling unless you pressed RMB.
Changes:

- Fixed an issue when reloading/switching weapon and going into a Slide/Roll at the same time. 

Several changes to the Zed Acid Puke Master:

- Acid Puke Master's Gas tank is slightly enlarged, making it easier to hit. 

- Acid Puke Master will now stand still a little bit longer before he is able to move again, giving the player a greater chance of running behind and hitting his gas tank.

- The Acid coming from the Acid Puke Master's vomit will now get removed when taking a Shower (and the Pool at the Aqua Park map). Very useful if you are hit by the vomit, low on Health and don't have any med-packs around.

- He is no longer immune to Explosive shots, but he only recieves 50% of the Explosive damage, making other weapon types a more viable option when trying to kill him.

- Added a Gas tank indicator that shows up when he is in puking state, making it easier to understand and see where to hit him when in this state.

- He can no longer be sucked in into the BS Void Creator.


- The boss Glitchface's second phase, when he's spawning the health destroyer beacon, will now yield 3 Damage points per second to the player instead of 1 when the beacon is active. It will also do 75 Damage points to every player instead of 50 if failing to destroy the beacon before the timer runs out and it explodes.

- Healing Done in Statistics is now working as intended.

Just some small tweaks and fixes for 0.613.

Fixes:

- Fixed an issue where the Lobby wouldn't close when the game was about to begin.

- Fixed an issue (most likely, cannot reproduce again) where the Inventory wouldn't spawn everytime when joining a server already in progress.

- A few places was not reachable by Zeds but by Players, this is now fixed.


Changes:

- Parkour Rolls in Statistics.

Here comes a bunch of stuff,fixes, changes and added stuff for 0.62.

Fixes:

- Fixed an issue when setting the FoV slider in the main menu and jumping into a lobby, the selected FoV would be forgotten and reverted to its standard value - 80.

- Fixed a HUD issue.

- Fixed a bug when Prestige:ing a class and all the Perks didn't reset correctly.

- Fixed an issue where you didn't always get the score by killing the Acid Puker Master when shooting at his Gas tank.

- Fixed the Scope on Sniper weapons not zooming correctly after changing View distance or Field of View in video settings.

- Fixed a health Bug when the Health Beacon Destroyer was active.

- Removed the ability to Taunt while in the pool at Aquaworld.

- Bosses can no longer Damage the player while they are standing still in various phases.

- Fixed an issue where the Bosses received damage from the BS Void Creator if they happened to jump into its core.

- The Steam achievement "Better get used to it!" did not work correctly in Multiplayer. This is now fixed.

Fixes:
